Interface JNode

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<JNode>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    JInstrumentalNode
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractJNode, JArrayNode, JObjectNode, JValueNode

    public interface JNode
extends java.lang.Iterable<JNode>
    Interface JNode represents operation are common for all types of node of tree.
    Author:
    krasnop@bellsouth.net (Alexei Krasnopolski)

      • getNode

        <K> JNode getNode(K selector)
        Returns child node of this node by selector. If type of this node is JNodeType.ARRAY a selector has to be Integer type and represents index of the array member. If type of this node is JNodeType.OBJECT a selector has to be String and represents key of object property.
        Type Parameters:
        K - type of the selector: Integer or String.
        Parameters:
        selector - is index or key.
